-- Fox Studio Signs Multiyear Film-Library Agreement With Starz
-- B y   R o b   G o l u m
-- 2013-07-30T16:09:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-30/fox-studio-signs-multiyear-film-library-agreement-with-starz.html
Starz, the premium cable TV network,
signed a multiyear licensing agreement to carry movies such as
“X-Men” and “Home Alone” from the library of  21st Century
Fox Inc. (FOXA)   The accord gives Starz rights to hundreds of Fox movies for
commercial-free play on the namesake Starz and Encore channels,
along with associated HD, on-demand, and Web offerings, the
companies said today in a statement. Financial terms weren’t
announced.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rob Golum in Los Angeles at 
